## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->
I'm using an excel template with some formulas(IRR, Data table) and saving the changes to a new file after adding values to few cells. But somehow the data table formula got removed in the new file.


## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

```javascript
  const Excel = require("exceljs");
  const workbook = new Excel.Workbook();
  const templateName = "./Book1.xlsx";
  workbook.xlsx.readFile(templateName).then((result) => {
    let worksheet1 = workbook.getWorksheet(1);

    const row1 = worksheet1.getRow(1);
    row1.getCell(6).value =  -199;
    row1.commit();
   workbook.xlsx.writeFile('Book2.xlsx');
});
```
So the Book1.xlsx is the template I'm using and Book2.xlsx is the new file with the changes. Datatable formula is removed in Book2.xlsx file.
Even if there are multiple workbooks in the template and I don't even edit in that particular workbook still the formula got removed.
## The expected behavior:
The formula should stay in place

